'''Egon Erzum''' (22 September 1904 – 14 October 1974) was a [[German people|German]] politician from the [[All-German Bloc/League of Expellees and Deprived of Rights|GB/BHE]] and later of the [[Christian Social Union of Bavaria]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Profile at the Landtag of Bavaria website|url=http://www.hdbg.de/parlament/content/persDetail.php?id=4168|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> 

He was one of the co-founders of the GB/BHE and member of the [[Landtag of Bavaria]] between 1954 and 1958. Following the demise of the party he affiliated to the [[Christian Social Union of Bavaria]]. He was also Mayor of [[Leutershausen]] from 1962 to 1965.

